headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times FROM WASHINGTON. The Difficulty between Messrs. Cutting and Breekinridge. PRESENT STATE OF THE QUARREL. Debates in Congress. MISCELLANEOUS INTELLIGENCE.

docs.lead_paragraph: The friends of Messrs. CUTTINGS and BRECKINRIDGE have been using every effort to-day to bring about a settlement without resort to arms. The prospect of peace brightens. Both the gentlemen are still out of this District. The excitement in the Senate about the GADSDEN Treaty continues.

headline.main: FROM HAVANA.; ARRIVAL OF THE BLACK WARRIOR. Account of her Seizure and Delivery. INTERESTING NEWS FROM CUBA.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Black Warrior, J. D. BULLOCK, Esq., Commander, arrived at this port last evening. She brings twenty-six passengers and nine hundred and sixty-one bales of Cotton. The Black Warrior was surrendered to Capt. BULLOCK on the 20th, when he again took possession.
